     object with the following structure containing the broken-
     out fields of a line in the password file.

	  /*   pwd.h	 4.1  83/05/03	*/

	  struct    passwd { /* see getpwent(3) */
	       char *pw_name;
	       char *pw_passwd;
	       int  pw_uid;
	       int  pw_gid;
	       int  pw_quota;
	       char *pw_comment;
	       char *pw_gecos;
	       char *pw_dir;
	       char *pw_shell;
	  };

	  struct passwd *getpwent(), *getpwuid(), *getpwnam();

     The fields _p_w__q_u_o_t_a and _p_w__c_o_m_m_e_n_t are  unused;  the  others
     have meanings described in _p_a_s_s_w_d(5).

     Searching of the password file is done using the _n_d_b_m  data-
     base access routines.  _S_e_t_p_w_e_n_t opens the database; _e_n_d_p_w_e_n_t
     closes it.  _G_e_t_p_w_u_i_d and _g_e_t_p_w_n_a_m search the database (open-
     ing  it  if  necessary)  for a matching _u_i_d or _n_a_m_e.  EOF is
     returned if there is no entry.




