     For programs wishing to read the entire  database,  _g_e_t_p_w_e_n_t
     reads the next line (opening the database if necessary).  In
     addition to opening the database, _s_e_t_p_w_e_n_t can  be  used  to
     make  _g_e_t_p_w_e_n_t  begin  its  search from the beginning of the
     database.

     _S_e_t_p_w_f_i_l_e changes the default password  file  to  _n_a_m_e  thus
     allowing  alternate password files to be used.  Note that it
     does _n_o_t close the  previous  file.   If  this  is  desired,
     _e_n_d_p_w_e_n_t should be called prior to it.

